<a href="mailto:dil@dil.com">Diluted</a> of the Erollisi Marr server on Oct. 27, 2000 at 06:37pm said...<br>
How to kill Innoruuk:
Upon getting to the second floor, the main thing you must do is clear it. Innoruuk can and DOES agro anything living on that floor of PoH on you once you agro him. Once you clear the floor, the rest is cake.

Get about 6 full groups. Hang out for a while outside the archway of Inno's room. Do NOT be in the archway, or Inno might agro you, grav flux you all over the zone, and wipe out chances of killing him for that night.

Now, set up groups. Shamans and Enchanters are a must. Pick a death touch candidate. Once you are ready, send in the DT candidate ahead of everyone. Once your hear Inno scream their name, thats your cue to rush in. Warrior stick on him. First thing that must be done is to PILLAGE ENCHANTMENT. Cleric buffs on Inno from a cleric of Inno can make a huge difference, or a dmg shield from a vampire might screw tanks over. After that, have the shamans immediatly malisement Inno, have necros scent inno, and have enchanters Tish him. It might take a few casts, but its worth it. Once those are all cast, have the shamans cast insects on him and he's as good as gone. Have EVERYONE throw every dot they have on inno... SAVE MANA. If you go oom too soon you might be doing more hurt than help because Inno might make a train(Ill explain later). After about 50%, nuke. Once he gets to a sliver of life, he WILL run, and his pathing will take him down his ramp to the first floor, and that might result in a huge train. This cannot happen. A smart idea would be to have everyone follow Inno, and every caster nuking... I think snares will work, but not sure. If he does get low, you'll have a train of about 3 mobs... if it is anymore just have a cleric log and have a monk/necro/SK FD next to corpse.

Thats it... Inno is a push over compared to CT, or vox in my opinion...<br><br>
